{
  "stem": "10181.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, by the police.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On-- on-- on the--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, in the evening.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah, we had to stay there, like I said.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And like I told you before, I woke up in the middle of the night when-- when Francesca came to say goodbye.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then, I know early in the morning, my mother tried to get in touch by phone-- there was a phone in the school, and everyone was lined up to make calls-- to my uncles in Holland.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had two-- two uncles from my father's side, the two brothers of my father who lived in Holland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One was Max Spiegel and the other one was Adolf Spiegel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I had an aunt, a sister of my mother, who had married a Dutch Jew and lived in a town called Enschede.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And apparently, she must have spoken to him sometime during the day or the next day, I don't quite remember the sequence, and made arrangements for us to go to Gennep, which was the-- Adolf.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was-- Adolf was the oldest brother of my father and had also been my father's partner in-- in the business.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I also remembered him well from-- still from-- from Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The other uncle, I knew him by name, and I'd been to his place in Holland on visit, but I-- I don't remember him from Germany.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He had left much earlier.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So a day or two later-- I-- it could have been a week later, I don't know the exact time-- we were-- went by train to Holland.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, it's-- it's a little bit vague.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I don't-- I-- as far as I remember, I went from the school to Holland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I know that my mother had been-- was allowed back to pick up things.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
